Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Korean War Veterans Memorial in Washington, D.C., honoring the veterans of the Korean War and their families. He presented a flag that was among those that graced the cases of fallen American heroes and expressed gratitude for President Trump's efforts in securing a promise from North Korea to return the remains of missing American soldiers. Pence also highlighted the progress being made towards a lasting peace on the Korean Peninsula and emphasized the importance of the United States' commitment to leave no one behind. He mentioned the upcoming construction of a Wall of Remembrance at the memorial to honor the fallen soldiers. Pence acknowledged the sacrifices made by the veterans and their families and assured them that their loved ones will never be forgotten. He concluded by expressing gratitude to all those who have served in the military and praying for the memory of the fallen and their families.